article.description: Lydia Bauer scored 19 points to lead Wisconsin-Green Bay (No. 11 ESPN/USA Today, No. 12 AP) to a 75-50 win over Youngstown State on Thursday night, giving the Phoenix their 36th straight regular season victory.
article.headline: Wisconsin-Green Bay cruises, improves to 16-0
article.linkText: Green Bay bullies Youngstown St., stays perfect
article.story:
GREEN BAY, Wis. -- Lydia Bauer scored 19 points to lead Wisconsin-Green Bay (No. 11 ESPN/USA Today, No. 12 AP) to a 75-50 win over Youngstown State on Thursday night, giving the Phoenix their 36th straight regular season victory.

Adrian Ritchie scored 17 points and Julie Wojta added 12 points and 11 rebounds for Green Bay (16-0, 6-0 Horizon League), which never trailed and led by 16 at halftime en route to extending its school-record win streak. The Phoenix also remained one of two unbeaten teams in the nation, along with top-ranked Baylor.

Brandi Brown had 21 points and 10 rebounds for Youngstown State (8-9, 2-4). The Penguins briefly made it interesting with a 8-3 run to open the second half but Green Bay's win was never in doubt.
